SIMPLE: milled
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Milled
<hw>Milled</hw> <pr>(m⟦icr⟧ld)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having been subjected to some process of milling.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <def>Having multiple fine
grooves on the rim, in the direction from obverse to reverse; -- of
coins. Coins of silver and gold were <ex>milled</ex> to make it
impossible for uncrupulous persons to shave small pieces from the edge
without detection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Milled cloth</b></col>, <cd>cloth that has been beaten in
a fulling mill.</cd> -- <col><b>Milled lead</b></col>, <cd>lead rolled
into sheets.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Millefiore glass</ent>⟦br⟧
